This information will help determine the benefits of habitat management, e.g. by creating meadows and how best to maintain woodland for bats and other associated species.
The number of bats has declined significantly over the last century in Scotland and throughout Britain.
They are under threat from construction and development projects that affect their nests and reduce habitat.
Windmills and lights can also cause risks, including fly paper and certain chemical treatments of building materials, as well as attacks from home cats.
Bats aren't really blind.
